<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 856/1999 of 22 April 1999 establishing a special framework of assistance for traditional ACP suppliers of bananas </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 856/1999, millega n&auml;hakse ette tavap&auml;rastele AKV banaanitarnijatele antava toetuse eriraamistik 22. aprill 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 130w thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 130w, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189c of the Treaty(2), </inglise>
<eesti> toimides koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu (2) artiklis 189c etten&auml;htud menetlusega </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas the European Union is bound by the undertakings it made to the ACP countries under the Lom&eacute; Convention, and more particularly Protocol 5 thereof, which seeks to guarantee maintenance for the ACP States of their advantages on the European market, access to that market in conditions that may not be less favourable than those that they have previously enjoyed and improvement of production and marketing conditions for ACP bananas; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1) Euroopa Liitu seovad AKV riikide ees Lom&eacute; konventsiooniga v&otilde;etud kohustused, eelk&otilde;ige selle protokoll 5, mille eesm&auml;rk on tagada AKV riikide eeliste s&auml;ilimine Euroopa turul, juurdep&auml;&auml;s nimetatud turule v&auml;hemalt sama soodsatel tingimustel kui varem ning AKV banaanide tootmise ja turustuse parandamine; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas the common organisation of the market in bananas established by Regulation (EEC) No 404/93(3) set the framework for continuing, on the Community market, the advantages enjoyed in the past by traditional ACP suppliers; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 404/93 (3) etten&auml;htud banaanituru &uuml;hise korraldusega kehtestatakse raamistik seni tavap&auml;rastele AKV tarnijatele kuulunud soodustuste j&auml;tkamiseks &uuml;henduse turul; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas, in particular, the trade arrangements with third countries established by Title IV of the said Regulation were designed to allow bananas produced by the ACP States, which are traditional suppliers to the Community, to be disposed of on the Community market providing an adequate income for the producers, in accordance with the Community's commitment set out above; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) eespool nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse IV jaotisega kehtestatud kolmandate riikidega kauplemise korra eesm&auml;rk on eelk&otilde;ige v&otilde;imaldada &uuml;henduse tavap&auml;raste tarnijate, AKV riikide toodetud banaanide realiseerimine &uuml;henduse turul, et koosk&otilde;las eespool nimetatud &uuml;henduse kohustusega tagada tootjatele piisav sissetulek; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas these trade arrangements have been amended by Regulation (EC) No 1637/98; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) nimetatud kauplemiskorda on muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1637/98; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas these trade modifications have substantially altered the market conditions for traditional ACP suppliers and might, in particular, harm the most disadvantaged suppliers; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) need muutused kauplemises on tavap&auml;raste AKV tarnijate jaoks turuolukorda oluliselt muutnud ning v&otilde;ivad kahjustada eelk&otilde;ige k&otilde;ige ebasoodsamas olukorras olevaid tarnijaid; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas particular efforts will thus be needed by traditional ACP suppliers to adapt to these new market conditions in order to maintain a presence on the Community market and to allow for the continuing viability of traditional ACP supplies; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) tavap&auml;rased AKV tarnijad peavad seet&otilde;ttu tegema erilisi j&otilde;upingutusi uute turutingimustega kohanemiseks, et s&auml;ilitada kohalolek &uuml;henduse turul ning tavap&auml;raste AKV tarnete eluj&otilde;ulisus; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas technical and financial assistance, additional to that provided for in the fourth ACP-EC Convention of Lom&eacute;, should therefore be granted to traditional ACP suppliers to enable them to adapt to new market conditions and in particular to improve competitiveness; whereas at the same time environment-friendly production and marketing methods which also respect social standards should be encouraged; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) seet&otilde;ttu tuleks tavap&auml;rastele AKV tarnijatele lisaks neljanda AKV- E&Uuml; Lom&eacute; konventsiooniga etten&auml;htud toetusele anda tehnilist ja rahalist toetust, et v&otilde;imaldada neil kohaneda uute turutingimustega ning eelk&otilde;ige parandada konkurentsiv&otilde;imet; samal ajal tuleks edendada keskkonnas&otilde;bralikke tootmis- ja turustusmeetodeid, mis oleksid kook&otilde;las ka sotsiaalsete tingimustega; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas, as this assistance should relate to the special efforts required as a consequence of the new market conditions, objective criteria should be fixed to determine the extent of such assistance; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) kuna see toetus peaks olema seotud uutest turutingimustest tulenevate eriliste j&otilde;upingutustega, tuleks kehtestada nimetatud toetuse ulatuse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramise objektiivsed kriteeriumid; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas, in order to ensure the appropriateness of such assistance with regard to the objectives pursued, this assistance should be temporary and should be gradually and smoothly phased out; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) see toetus peaks olema ajutine ning tuleks l&otilde;petada j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult ja sujuvalt, et tagada eespool nimetatud toetuse otstarbekus seoses taotletavate eesm&auml;rkidega; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas, to facilitate implementation of these provisions, a procedure involving close cooperation between the Member States and the Commission should be established, </inglise>
<eesti> 10) nimetatud s&auml;tete rakendamise soodustamiseks tuleks ette n&auml;ha liikmesriikide ja komisjoni tihedat koost&ouml;&ouml;d h&otilde;lmav menetlus, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A special framework for technical and financial assistance is hereby established to assist traditional ACP suppliers of bananas to adapt to the new market conditions following the amendments made to the common organisation of the market in bananas by Regulation (EC) No 1637/98. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga n&auml;hakse ette tehnilise ja rahalise toetuse eriraamistik, et aidata tavap&auml;rastel AKV banaanitarnijatel kohaneda m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1637/98 banaanituru &uuml;hises korralduses tehtud muudatustest tulenevate uute turutingimustega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> This special framework shall be implemented for a period not exceeding ten years starting on 1 January 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda eriraamistikku rakendatakse alates 1. jaanuarist 1999 maksimaalselt k&uuml;mne aasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> - "traditional ACP suppliers" means the ACP countries listed in the Annex, </inglise>
<eesti> - tavap&auml;rased AKV tarnijad - lisas loetletud AKV riigid, </eesti>
<inglise> - "bananas" means fresh or dried bananas covered by CN code 0803, except for plantains. </inglise>
<eesti> - banaanid - CN-koodi 0803 alla kuuluvad v&auml;rsked v&otilde;i kuivatatud banaanid, v&auml;lja arvatud jahubanaanid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Traditional ACP suppliers shall be eligible for technical and financial assistance. </inglise>
<eesti> Tavap&auml;rased AKV tarnijad saavad tehnilist ja rahalist toetust. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Technical and financial assistance shall be granted at the request of the ACP to contribute to the implementation of programmes aiming: </inglise>
<eesti> Tehnilist ja rahalist toetust antakse AKV riikide taotlusel selliste programmide rakendamise toetuseks, mille eesm&auml;rk on: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) to improve competitiveness in the banana sector, in particular through: </inglise>
<eesti> a) parandada konkurentsiv&otilde;imet banaaniturul, eelk&otilde;ige: </eesti>
<inglise> - increasing productivity, without causing damage to the environment, </inglise>
<eesti> - suurendades tootlikkust ilma keskkonda kahjustamata, </eesti>
<inglise> - improving quality, including phytosanitary measures, </inglise>
<eesti> - parandades kvaliteeti, sealhulgas f&uuml;tosanitaarmeetmeid, </eesti>
<inglise> - adapting production, distribution or marketing methods to meet the quality standards provided for in Article 2 of Regulation (EEC) No 404/93, </inglise>
<eesti> - viies tootmis-, levitamis- ja turustusmeetmed vastavusse m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 404/93 artiklis 2 s&auml;testatud kvaliteedistandarditega, </eesti>
<inglise> - establishing producers' organisations which have as their objective the improvement of the marketing and competitiveness of their products and the development of systems of certifying environment-friendly production methods, including fair-trade bananas, </inglise>
<eesti> - asutades selliseid tootjaorganisatsioone, mille eesm&auml;rk on parandada oma toodete turustust ja konkurentsiv&otilde;imet ning arendada keskkonnas&otilde;bralike tootmismeetodite sertifitseerimise s&uuml;steeme, sealhulgas &otilde;iglast banaanikaubandust, </eesti>
<inglise> - developing a production and/or marketing strategy to meet the requirements of the market in the light of the Community's common organisation of the market in bananas, </inglise>
<eesti> - arendades sellist tootmis- ja/v&otilde;i turustusstrateegiat, mis vastaks &uuml;henduse banaanituru &uuml;hise korraldusega seotud turun&otilde;uetele, </eesti>
<inglise> - assisting with training, market intelligence, the development of environment-friendly production methods including fair-trade bananas, improving the distribution infrastructure and improving commercial and financial services to banana producers; </inglise>
<eesti> - toetades v&auml;lja&otilde;pet, turu-uuringuid, keskkonnas&otilde;bralikke tootmismeetodeid, sealhulgas &otilde;iglast banaanikaubandust, parandades jaotusinfrastruktuuri ning banaanitootjatele pakutavaid kaubandus- ja finantsteenuseid; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) to support diversification where improvement in the competitiveness of the banana sector is not sustainable. </inglise>
<eesti> b) toetada mitmekesistamist, kui banaanisektori konkurentsiv&otilde;ime p&uuml;sivalt ei parane. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall decide on the eligibility of the programmes referred to in Article 3 after consultation with the traditional ACP suppliers concerned in accordance with the procedures laid down in Article 6. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 3 osutatud programmide k&otilde;lblikkuse otsustab komisjon artiklis 6 s&auml;testatud korras p&auml;rast konsulteerimist asjaomaste tavap&auml;raste AKV tarnijatega. </eesti>
